# role-based-access-model

Core user roles and permissions hierarchy:

1. Player Role (Base Level)
- Basic team member access
- View team schedules and matches
- Participate in team chat
- Access personal statistics and achievements
- Join/leave teams via invitation or team code

2. Captain Role (Extended Access)
Primary file: src/components/onboarding/OnboardingFlow.tsx
- Team management capabilities:
  - Create and configure teams
  - Manage team roster
  - Send player invitations
  - Set team preferences and metadata
- Elevated communication features:
  - Pin important messages
  - Send captain announcements
  - Manage team communications

Role Assignment and Management:
- Captain status assigned during team creation
- One captain per team enforced
- Role persistence across sessions
- Role-specific UI elements and feature access

Onboarding Flow Control:
- Distinct workflows for player vs captain roles
- Different data collection requirements:
  - Players: Basic profile information
  - Captains: Additional team configuration data
- Role-specific validation rules

Permission Structure:
File: src/lib/auth/useAuth.ts
- Feature access controlled by role flags
- Hierarchical permission inheritance
- Session-based role verification
- Role-specific navigation paths

The role system implements a two-tier access model focused on team management and player participation, with clear separation between administrative (captain) and member (player) capabilities.

